description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are a dynamic, well organised individual who inspires others you could be the person The Talent for Care &amp; Apprenticeship Team are looking for! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Team can offer a secondment/fixed term full time position working with the Apprenticeship lead and Learning co-ordinator to manage aspects of development programmes and apprenticeships for internal staff as well as new recruits. The position is for one year from January 2021. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The skills and knowledge you will require include, great IT skills, time management, ability to be self-sufficient and work autonomously. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a clinical/care background and a great understanding of apprenticeships. Your communication skills will be excellent as you will be communicating across a wide range of staff and external partners. You will have experience in training/presenting and feel comfortable in giving clear concise information to others - both face to face and virtual. This is a fabulous opportunity to join an evolving organisation working for a friendly and cohesive team with a very broad and interesting portfolio. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a band 5 role and the hours of business are Monday to Friday between 0800 – 1800 and does not attract enhancements. Hours can be worked across a four day or five-day week. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;During the pandemic the team are working predominantly from home and will continue to do so. As the Covid situation evolves we will adapt work patterns in line with Government and organisational policy. There will be an expectation that there will be some face to face duties required but any such work with be conducted in a safe way. If/as Covid comes under control, face to face duties may increase.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be on the 26th november, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please visit out Facebook and Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJane StringerJob titleApprenticeship LeadEmail addressjane.stringer@nsft.nhs.ukTelephone number01603 421564&lt;/p&gt;
